@robertwb Thank you. I agree with you. Returned the exception to its previous state and added a TODO there with a JIRA issue. 

We were checking for error propagation only with the DirectRunner and that was still raising the exception. This changes unifies both runners again. (Still keeping the assert in the TestPipeline in case a future runner only sets the state to failed without raising an exception.)

PTAL.
